@60000 = ~Wands are 1 1/4 ft. long and slender. They are made of ivory, bone, or wood and are usually tipped with something—metal, crystal, stone, and so on. They are fragile and tend to break easily. Because of this, they are often kept in cases.

Wands are powered by charges, each use costing one or more charges (depending on the item). When a wand runs out of charges, it is consumed and destroyed.

STATISTICS:

Weight: 1~


//Nahal's Reckless Dweomer
@60053 = ~Wand of Nahal's Reckless Dweomer~
@60054 = ~The Wild Mage's ultimate last-resort, a wild surge is purposefully invoked; the result might be beneficial to the Mage, or it might be completely disastrous: this is the risk the Wild Mage takes in casting Nahal's Reckless Dweomer.

When activated, select a known spell to attempt to cast; the wand releases a sudden flood of wild magical energy. The Wild Mage hopes to seize and shape that energy into a desired spell effect. The attempt usually fails, but something almost always occurs in the process -- the actual effect of the wand is determined randomly by a dice roll on the Wild Surge Table (see the manual for more details).

Because the release of energy is planned, the wand's caster level (%magnitude%) is added to the dice roll. If the result indicates success, the Mage has shaped the magical energy into the desired effect. More often than not, the effect is completely unexpected.

STATISTICS:
(Invocation/Evocation)

Charge abilities:
– Nahal's Reckless Dweomer
  – Pick a known spell
  – Wild surge occurs that attempts to cast the selected spell
  Range: Special
  Duration: Special
  Area of Effect: Special
  Saving Throw: Special

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Spook
@60055 = ~Wand of Spook~
@60056 = ~This wand's effect plays upon natural fears to cause the target creature to perceive the wielder as someone or something inimical, which then appears to advance upon it in a threatening manner. If the creature does not make a successful save vs. Wand, it turns and flees at maximum speed as far from the wielder as possible. Undead are completely unaffected.

STATISTICS:
(Invocation/Evocation)

Charge abilities:
– Spook
  – Target flees at maximum speed as far from the wielder as possible
  Range: 30 ft.
  Duration: 3 rounds
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Saving vs. Wand negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Spook (CL > 1)
@60057 = ~Wand of Spook~
@60058 = ~This wand's effect plays upon natural fears to cause the target creature to perceive the wielder as someone or something inimical, which then appears to advance upon it in a threatening manner. If the creature does not make a successful save vs. Wand, it turns and flees at maximum speed as far from the wielder as possible. The creature suffers a Saving Throw penalty of %magnitude%. Undead are completely unaffected.

STATISTICS:
(Invocation/Evocation)

Charge abilities:
– Spook
  – Target flees at maximum speed as far from the wielder as possible
  Range: 30 ft.
  Duration: 3 rounds
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Saving vs. Wand (-%magnitude% penalty) negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Dancing Lights
@60059 = ~Wand of Dancing Lights~
@60060 = ~This wand creates up to four glowing spheres of light (such as evidenced by will-o-wisps) or one faintly glowing, vaguely humanoid shape, somewhat similar to a fire elemental. The dancing lights move randomly without concentration upon such movement by the wielder. Although the lights cause no physical harm, they can distract enemies until either their duration expires or dispersed by weapon or magic.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Dancing Lights
  – 50% chance to summon 4 distracting lights
  – 50% chance to summon 1 distracting humanoid light
  Range: Sight
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Bless
@60061 = ~Wand of Bless~
@60062 = ~With activation, this wand releases the power of a prayerful blessing, raising the morale of friendly creatures by +1. Furthermore, it raises their attack and damage rolls by +1. The wielder determines a point (up to 40 ft. away) where the effect will occur, affecting all creatures in a 15-ft. radius centered on the point selected by the wielder (thus, affected creatures leaving the area are still subject to the effects; those entering the area after are not).

STATISTICS:
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Charge abilities:
– Bless
  – Morale +1
  – Attack rolls +1
  – Damage rolls +1
  Range: 40 ft.
  Duration: 1 turn
  Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Command (Olvyn?)
@60063 = ~Wand of Command~
@60064 = ~Upon activation, this wand allows the wielder to command another creature for a single round. Creatures with 6 or more Hit Dice (or experience levels) are entitled to a Saving Throw vs. Wand to ignore the command.

STATISTICS:
(Enchantment/Charm)

Charge abilities:
– Command
  – Charm target for 1 round
  Range: 90 ft.
  Duration: 1 round
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw:
  – Save vs. Wand to negate (if target has > 5 HD)
  – Otherwise: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Cure Light Wounds
@60065 = ~Wand of Cure Light Wounds~
@60066 = ~Upon activation, this wand causes 8 points of wound or other injury damage to the target's body to be healed. This healing cannot affect creatures without corporeal bodies, nor can it cure wounds of creatures not living or of extraplanar origin.

Curing is permanent only insofar as the creature does not sustain further damage; caused wounds will heal—or can be cured—just as any normal injury.

STATISTICS:
(Necromancy)

Charge abilities:
– Cure Light Wounds
  – Healed for 8 hit points
  Range: Touch
  Duration: Permanent
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Detect Evil
@60067 = ~Wand of Detect Evil~
@60068 = ~Upon activation, this wand reveals emanations of evil from any creature. Any evil creature within the range of the spell will glow red briefly.

STATISTICS:
(Divination)

Charge abilities:
– Detect Evil
  – Causes Evil creatures in range to glow red briefly
  Duration: Instant
  Area of Effect: Self, 30-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Entangle (Olvyn?)
@60069 = ~Wand of Entangle~
@60070 = ~When used, this wand causes plants in the area of effect to entangle enemies within the area. The grasses, weeds, bushes, and even trees wrap, twist, and entwine about the creatures, holding them fast for the duration if they fail a Save vs. Wand. An entangled creature can still attack, but receives a -2 penalty to its Armor Class.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Entangle
  – Reduce movement speed to 5%
  – Armor class -2 penalty
  Range: Visual range
  Duration: 1 turn
  Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Magic Stone (Olvyn?)
@60071 = ~Wand of Magical Stone~
@60072 = ~When activated, this wand causes a pebble to be temporarily enchanted, which is then hurled or slung at an opponent. The stone automatically hits, dealing 3d4 damage to the target (+3d4 more if target undead).

